00:44:25.810 --> 00:44:28.580
and asking them what they think.

00:44:28.580 --> 00:44:31.980
But yes, I guess the answer is
no, there isn't a specific ratio

00:44:31.980 --> 00:44:32.860
for too high.

00:44:36.607 --> 00:44:39.780
 AMANDA: All right, I'm just going
to roll on into the next question

00:44:39.780 --> 00:44:46.540
because there are a
lot of questions here.

00:44:46.540 --> 00:44:49.490
There’s a bullet point that
said, ‘Change images

00:44:49.490 --> 00:44:52.430
or icons that represent
an idea alone.’

00:44:52.430 --> 00:44:54.433
Are you able to clarify
that a bit more?

00:44:54.433 --> 00:44:55.500
 ALLIE: Yes.

00:44:56.567 --> 00:44:57.700
Let’s think of a good example.

00:45:07.067 --> 00:45:08.580
OK, one good example.

00:45:08.580 --> 00:45:12.520
Say you offer two services:
you offer coding services

00:45:12.520 --> 00:45:15.320
and you offer design services,
and you have a landing page

00:45:15.320 --> 00:45:18.670
where somebody can read about the
services, and then click on one

00:45:18.670 --> 00:45:22.310
of two buttons to either go learn
more about your coding services

00:45:22.310 --> 00:45:24.680
or learn more about
your design services.

00:45:24.680 --> 00:45:28.970
If you're coding services button,
instead of saying, Learn more

00:45:28.970 --> 00:45:32.680
about my coding services,
if it has, like, a bracket

00:45:33.700 --> 00:45:39.150
or some other symbol that represents
code, and that's what you're using

00:45:39.150 --> 00:45:42.810
to communicate that that's
what this button is for,

00:45:42.810 --> 00:45:44.440
that is not a strong choice.

00:45:46.380 --> 00:45:51.360
I'm not an expert in autism, but my
understanding is that many people

00:45:51.360 --> 00:45:54.150
who are neurodivergent
or on that spectrum have

00:45:54.150 --> 00:46:00.660
a hard time connecting a symbol to
a meaning for that symbol, right?

00:46:00.660 --> 00:46:03.510
So you're just
creating uncertainty.

00:46:03.510 --> 00:46:05.660
You’re creating a
little bit of confusion,

00:46:05.661 --> 00:46:07.060
whereas it's so much easier

00:46:07.060 --> 00:46:10.590
for you to just say
what that button is for.

00:46:10.590 --> 00:46:13.710
If you want to have that
symbol near the button

00:46:13.710 --> 00:46:17.940
or after the description, that's
great, that's fine, that's adorable.

00:46:17.940 --> 00:46:22.870
But using a symbol alone
to communicate a concept,

00:46:22.870 --> 00:46:26.460
especially a choice,
is not a strong idea,

00:46:26.460 --> 00:46:29.060
because you are isolating people
who would struggle to understand

00:46:29.061 --> 00:46:29.867
what that means.

00:46:34.220 --> 00:46:35.813
 AMANDA: Excellent example.

00:46:37.290 --> 00:46:38.440
Thank you, Allie.

00:46:39.470 --> 00:46:40.350
Next question.

00:46:40.350 --> 00:46:44.610
There's another in the Do
you need to... There’s a part

00:46:44.610 --> 00:46:48.890
about ...remove things that
move or change automatically.

00:46:48.890 --> 00:46:52.370
Does this include micro
animations, hover effects?

00:46:53.630 --> 00:46:56.840
Leah would love to learn more
about how these slight movements

00:46:56.840 --> 00:46:59.700
aren't accessible
to as many clients.

00:46:59.700 --> 00:47:00.433
 ALLIE: Yes.

00:47:01.750 --> 00:47:06.630
I would love for somebody whose
profession is accessibility

00:47:06.630 --> 00:47:09.640
to chime in here as well,
because I've heard kind

00:47:09.640 --> 00:47:16.570
of some dissenting opinions from...
To me, as somebody

00:47:16.570 --> 00:47:19.680
who does have anxiety and who does
end up in the middle of Target,

00:47:19.680 --> 00:47:24.320
not knowing what to do, if I'm
trying to find where I'm trying

00:47:24.320 --> 00:47:27.410
to go on your website, if I'm
trying to start my user journey

00:47:27.410 --> 00:47:32.650
or find the next step in my user
journey and things are moving

00:47:32.650 --> 00:47:37.000
and distracting my attention,
I'm distracted, right?

00:47:37.000 --> 00:47:38.600
And that's not what you want.

00:47:38.600 --> 00:47:42.180
I think something like a
hover animation is fine

00:47:42.180 --> 00:47:45.250
because my search is
already focused there.

00:47:45.250 --> 00:47:48.690
So if I touch something and it
moves, that's almost kind

00:47:48.690 --> 00:47:52.021
of an expected behavior,
so that's not really going

00:47:52.022 --> 00:47:53.430
to bother me as much.

00:47:53.430 --> 00:47:57.650
But if I'm reading some really
intent content, or I'm looking

00:47:57.650 --> 00:48:02.090
through a list of things, and this
other thing is hovering or moving

00:48:02.090 --> 00:48:05.740
or shaking, that's bothering
me, that's distracting me.

00:48:07.360 --> 00:48:11.440
So I would omit it as a designer.

00:48:11.440 --> 00:48:16.540
I would omit any movement that is not
directly helping the user accomplish

00:48:16.540 --> 00:48:17.540
what they're trying to do.

00:48:19.350 --> 00:48:21.360
I'm more than open,
though, to people

00:48:21.360 --> 00:48:24.140
in the chat arguing
back against that,

00:48:24.140 --> 00:48:26.330
because I'm sure there are things
I'm not thinking about there,

00:48:26.330 --> 00:48:31.402
but that's my reasoning
for minimizing movement

00:48:31.402 --> 00:48:32.750
as much as possible,

00:48:32.750 --> 00:48:35.328
especially if it's movement
that cannot be stopped

00:48:35.329 --> 00:48:38.560
and cannot be paused or cannot
be controlled in that way.

00:48:43.294 --> 00:48:44.040
 AMANDA: Thanks, Allie.

